quran[11]{c,v,t}:
  33,63,"The people question you concerning the Hour. Say, ‘Its knowledge is only with Allah.’ What do you know, maybe the Hour is near"
  33,64,Indeed Allah has cursed the faithless and prepared for them a blaze
  33,65,"in which they will remain forever, and will not find any guardian or helper"
  33,66,"The day when their faces are turned about in the Fire, they will say, ‘We wish we had obeyed Allah and obeyed the Apostle!’"
  33,67,"They will say, ‘Our Lord! We obeyed our leaders and elders, and they led us astray from the way.’"
  33,68,Our Lord! Give them a double punishment and curse them with a mighty curse.’
  33,69,"O you who have faith! Do not be like those who offended Moses, whereat Allah cleared him of what they alleged, and he was distinguished in Allah’s sight"
  33,70,"O you who have faith! Be wary of Allah, and speak upright words"
  33,71,He will rectify your conduct for you and forgive you your sins. Whoever obeys Allah and His Apostle will certainly achieve a great success
  33,72,"Indeed We presented the Trust to the heavens and the earth and the mountains, but they refused to undertake it and were apprehensive of it; but man undertook it. Indeed he is most unjust and ignorant"
  33,73,"Allah will surely punish the hypocrites, men and women, and the polytheists, men and women, and Allah will turn clemently to the faithful, men and women, and Allah is all-forgiving, all-merciful"